sub_title: Carving a new path in healthcare ✨ Nurse in training
summary: After more than a decade in different industries across the commercial field, both in Chile and overseas, I am in search of a new path. As of January 2023 I am transitioning towards a new career and a new profession in the healthcare sector of the Netherlands. From a place where science and humanitarian aid converge, I wish to be able to contribute further with my work and knowledge in caring for the physical and mental well-being of fellow human beings in the years to come. You are invited to join and to follow me in this new journey!

projects: [{'title': "Building a roadmap for the future of the RDW's Test Center", 'date': {'start': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}, 'end': {'month': 12, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}}, 'description': 'The RDW faces the challenge of re-locating their current Test Center based in Lelystad. In line with the current developments in the automotive industry, mostly ignited by the rise of automation and driver-less technologies, the RDW has projected the construction of a New Test Center which can cater also for the testing of all these new technologies and attract new partners and customers, given the new business opportunities that are available. The research starts with an understanding of the current situation of the existing Test Center via a detailed 360-degree assessment. This is followed by a gap analysis, considering the situation today versus the envisioned future. Once the gap is described, a roadmap with recommendations towards the desired outcome is designed and proposed.
